    <h3>Hiroshima Homestay Programme</h3>
    <p>Hiroshima Singapore Association (HSA) was established in 1995 to promote mutual understanding between Singapore and Hiroshima.  The Department has been organising student exchange homestay programmes with HSA since 1998.  Every year, students who participated in the programme have learnt about Japanese culture as well as Japanese businesses by attending flower arrangement and tea ceremony workshops, meeting with local university students, visiting companies and factories, and meeting with businesspeople in Hiroshima.</p>
